      • RetrieveCountryByName

        public Country RetrieveCountryByName(java.lang.String name)
        Public accessor for retrieveCountryByName Creates a temporary country to return which is equal to the result of calling retrieveCountryByName () passing in the pre-defined String and the root node to begin search from. Cast's the data from the returned node to type Country so it can be passed out.
        Parameters:
        name - Pre-defined String to search for.
        Returns:
        Country that was associated with String, or null.

      • RetrievePartners

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> RetrievePartners(java.lang.String countryName)
        Public accessor to retrieve all trade partners of a selected Country. Creates a string which is constructed from the retrievePartners method. Following this a List is created and populated from the returned String. This List now contains all the Countries whose list of trading partners contained the Country's name. After that, a check is done for the Country in question's trade partners to see if any are missing and a validation is done to make sure the first link in the list isn't null.
        Parameters:
        countryName - Chosen Country to search for.
        Returns:
        List of all the Countries who trade with the chosen Country.

      • PredictiveSearch

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> PredictiveSearch(java.lang.String prefix)
        Public method used to return a list of Country names to be used in predictive search. Initial check to see if the search string isn't null, then populates a List of Country names that are retrieved as a String from predictiveSearch. The list is sorted before it's returned.
        Parameters:
        prefix - Search parameter passed in from UI.
        Returns:
        List of results.
